\section desc Description
Framework module for common particle candidate manupulation

\subsection interface Public interface
- CandSelectorBase: base class for all candidate selectors. It is a specialization of the
generic selector module SelectorProducer.

\subsection modules Modules
- candmodules::CandCombiner: combine pairs of candidates. The collection names that
have to be combined and their charge combination is specified by the user. A string
can also specify the selection cut on the composite candidates.<br>
Examples of configuration for this module are the following:
\htmlonly
<pre>
  module ZCandidates = CandCombiner {
    string decay = "muons@+ muons@-"
    string cut = "86.0 < mass < 96.0"
  }

  module BsCandidates = CandCombiner {
    string decay = "JPsiCandidates PhiCandidats"
    string cut = "2.8 < mass < 3.4"
  }
</pre>
Everywhere, charge conjugate final state is implied. E.g.: <tt>"x@+ y@-"</tt> selects
both decays to <i>x<sup>+</sup>y<sup>-</sup></i> and <i>x<sup>-</sup>y<sup>+</sup></i>.

\endhtmlonly

- candmodules::CandReducer: clones a collection of candidates removing all daughters and external
components, leaving only kinematic information. This is ment to produce a "light" collection
of candiadates just containing kimenatics information for very fast analysis purpose.
Example of configuration for this module is the following:
\htmlonly
<pre>
  module caloTowerFourVectorOnly = CandReducer {
    string src = "caloTowerCandidates"
  }
</pre>
\endhtmlonly

- candmodules::CandSelector: selects candidates from a collection and saves their clones in 
a new collection. The selection can be specified by the user as a string. <br>
Examples of configuration for this module are the following:
\htmlonly
<pre>
  module goodMuons = CandSelector {
    string src = "allMuons"
    string cut = "pt > 5.0"
  }

  module goodZ = CandSelector {
    string src = "allZ"
    string cut = "86.0 < mass < 96.0"
  }
</pre>
\endhtmlonly


